{
  "stem": "4247.5",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Russians were coming there from Romania to Budapest, on official business and on holidays.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I organized a truck.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "The truck came out to the peasant place.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And we have loaded up a truck full of flour.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And we brought this flour into Budapest.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "I don't think anybody in Budapest, at that stage, had a truck full of flour.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And I gave some to my uncle, the baker.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I give some to my-- my auntie.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And I sold the rest of it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] It was very difficult times-- very difficult times, when it was no life danger anymore, in the sense we had it a few months before.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "But people were dying like flies from lack of food.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "The Russians were in, and the Russians were the conquerors, and they let us know that they were conquerors.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And they were raping.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "They were taking watches away and doing all sorts of vicious things.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "I remember my cousin had to sit behind a wardrobe-- a young girl-- which we put on a corner.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And she was sitting behind that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And when the Russian soldiers came in, looking for [NON-ENGLISH], for girls-- I was-- I mean, my uncle was there.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "I was the only young man.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "I took him around the house and proved that there's no girls here.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In one of the rooms, an old man-- and old Jewish man-- died.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And in those early times, it was very difficult to-- to bury people.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Right?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So this man was a religious Jewish man.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was lying there in state, with a couple of candles at the head.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And when these drunken, primitive Russian soldiers saw the old man, they said 'stare papa.' It means 'old man.' And they turned around, and they fled.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
